liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Half back Adam Clune takes on the line and pokes his nose through from 5 metres out. He just manages to get an arm free and pops a pass to Dylan Lucas to crash over, but the pass looked very, shall we say, flat. Warriors fans are fuming as the replay is shown. Very close call. Regardless, it's a try in the books and Ponga converts. 16-10. The Knights are closing.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Newcastle strikes first in the second half on a dubious pass

children.content: Half back Adam Clune takes on the line and pokes his nose through from 5 metres out. He just manages to get an arm free and pops a pass to Dylan Lucas to crash over, but the pass looked very, shall we say, flat.
Warriors fans are fuming as the replay is shown. Very close call.
Regardless, it's a try in the books and Ponga converts. 16-10. The Knights are closing.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Knights have done a remarkable job fighting their way back into this match after conceding three tries and barely touching the ball for the first 15 minutes. This half-time score is similar to last week's 16-6 deficit against Canberra, when Newcastle stormed back and ended up winning in extra time. The Warriors can't afford to let up here and I can't imagine they would in front of these home fans.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: Warriors lead Newcastle 16-4
